meta {
  name: 3.1 Earn money - easy RAG
  type: http
  seq: 1
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/ask/easy-rag
  body: json
  auth: inherit
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "question": "Can I earn money from the newsletter? If so, how?"
  }
}

settings {
  encodeUrl: true
}

docs {
  # Beat 3 — RAG by config (same answer, no wiring)

  Same question as `1.1` and `2.1`, but this endpoint has **no retrieval code** —
  it's driven entirely by the `quarkus.langchain4j.easy-rag.*` properties.

  **Expected:** essentially the same grounded answer as `2.1 naive RAG`.

  The point isn't a new answer — it's that you got the *same* answer with the
  hand-written retriever/augmentor deleted. Show this right after `2.1` and point
  at `application.properties`.
}
